  "title": "VMware Engineer",
  "description": "<p><p>Requirement :<br />4+ years of experience as a System Administrator in enterprise IT environments.<br />Strong expertise in Microsoft Azure (IaaS, PaaS, Networking, Cost Management).<br />Hands-on experience with VMware, ESXi, and Windows (Wintel) administration.<br />Proficiency in Terraform, Bicep, ARM Templates, and Infrastructure as Code.<br />Experience with Azure DevOps, GitHub Actions, PowerShell, and Azure CLI.<br />Knowledge of AKS, Docker, and container platforms.<br />Experience in monitoring, logging, security, and governance in Azure.<br /></p><p>Responsibilities :<br />Administer and support virtual servers and hosts in a corporate production environment.<br />Provide hands-on support for VMware, ESXi, and Wintel (Windows Server) administration.<br />Design, deploy, and manage Microsoft Azure infrastructure using IaaS and PaaS services <br />Develop and maintain infrastructure usingTerraform, Bicep, and ARM Templates<br />Participate in<br />incident, problem, and change management aligned with ITIL Foundation practices.</p><p><p>.</p></p></p>",
